The paper focuses on the development of a microservice-based reference architecture for reusing and integrating components for mobile app optimization. This involves software engineering (cs.SE) aspects such as architecture design and reuse, programming languages (cs.PL) for implementing the microservices, distributed computing (cs.DC) for the communication between the microservices, deep learning (cs.DL) for some of the optimization techniques, and systems and control (cs.SY) for the potential impact on the overall system performance.
